<% content_for(:title) { "About | mbuzz" } %>

<%= render "layouts/nav" %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-white">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight">
        Built by marketers who got tired of overpaying
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-8 text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        We spent years wrestling with GA4 limitations, platform-reported vanity metrics,
        and enterprise tools that cost more than they were worth.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        So we built the attribution platform we wished existed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Story Section -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Our story</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray">
        <p>
          It started with a spreadsheet. A massive, unwieldy spreadsheet trying to reconcile
          what Google said, what Facebook said, and what our actual revenue numbers showed.
          None of it matched. None of it ever matched.
        </p>

        <p>
          The spreadsheet was powered by a multi-source Python ETL we'd cobbled together,
          pulling data from every ad platform, CRM, and analytics tool we used. The goal?
          Build a bottom-up marketing forecast we could actually trust. Reconcile channel
          spend with attributed revenue. Figure out what was actually working.
        </p>

        <p>
          We tried the enterprise tools. Amplitude and Mixpanel wanted thousands per month
          for features we'd use maybe twice. Segment charged us to route events to yet another
          tool — adding a middle layer of cost without actually solving attribution. And GA4?
          Google took away all the attribution models we actually used — first-touch, linear,
          time-decay — replacing them with a black box we couldn't inspect.
        </p>

        <p>
          The tools that were supposed to help us understand our marketing were working
          against us. Platforms grading their own homework. Client-side scripts getting
          blocked by 30% of browsers. Data locked behind paywalls and export restrictions.
        </p>

        <p>
          We knew there had to be a better way. Server-side tracking that actually captures
          everything. Attribution models you can inspect and customize. Pricing that doesn't
          require a board meeting. Data you own and can export anytime.
        </p>

        <p>
          So we built it. mbuzz is the attribution platform we wished existed — and now it does.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Believe Section -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-12">What we believe</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Your data belongs to you</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Not locked behind export restrictions. Not held hostage when you want to leave.
            Export everything, anytime, in formats you can actually use.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Models you can understand</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Our rule-based models are fully transparent. Data-driven models use proven
            algorithms you can tune and customize. No unexplainable black boxes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Simple pricing, no surprises</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            No sales calls required. No enterprise minimums. Start free, scale affordably.
            You should know exactly what you'll pay before you sign up.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Server-side by default</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Client-side tracking is broken. Ad blockers, privacy extensions, and browser
            restrictions mean you're missing 30% of your data. We fix that.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Company Info Section -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The company</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
        mbuzz is built by <strong>Forebrite Pty Ltd</strong>, an Australian software company
        focused on building tools that respect both your data and your budget.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-500">
        ABN 64 671 038 958<br>
        Sydney, Australia
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-blue-600">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
        Ready to try it?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-blue-100 mb-8">
        Start free. No credit card required. No sales calls.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
        <%= link_to "Get Started Free", signup_path, class: "px-8 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-blue-600 bg-white hover:bg-blue-50 rounded-md transition-all" %>
        <%= link_to "Read the Docs", docs_path('getting-started'), class: "px-8 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-white border border-white/30 hover:bg-white/10 rounded-md transition-all" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<%= render "layouts/footer" %>
